Package: peaceBooksR
Type: Package
Title: Peace Books Prepared For the Paris Peace Conference 
Version: 0.5
Authors@R: person(given = "Stanislav",
           family = "Pej≈°a",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "spejsa@purdue.edu",
           comment = c(ORCID = "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5057-262X"))
Maintainer: The package maintainer <spejsa@purdue.edu>
Description: This package contains text of the Peace Books prepared by 
    the Historical Section of the British Foreign Office and published in 1920. 
    The package contains the texts of each volumes and and then the files that
    contain all texts in ine file. 
    In the dataset peace_books_pages each line of text correspond to to a page, 
    in the dataset peace_books_volumes, each line corresponds to 
    the content of the whole volume.
    THe package also contains datset peace_books_authorities that contains data 
    extracted from the list of refrences from each volume with the key 
    bibliographic metadata.
    The datset peace_books_sentiment contains tokens that were matched against 
    the `Bing` sentiment dictinary. These tokens are associated with a sentiment
    value, as well as thei lemmas, POS tags, and if available with the name 
    entity recognition (NER) value. 
    The corpora contains only the body of texts, section titles, footnotes, 
    running headers, tables, indices, and list of references (authorities) 
    were removed.
